  "sentences": [
    {
      "en": "By lunchtime, Coco was hungry enough to eat two full meals: rice, vegetables, and a bowl of hot soup.",
      "zh": "到了午餐時間，Coco 餓到可以吃下兩份正餐：白飯、蔬菜，還有一碗熱湯。"
    },
    {
      "en": "Wei, it turned out, almost never ate breakfast, which was part of why he cared so much about his favorite drink.",
      "zh": "後來發現 Wei 幾乎從來不吃早餐，這也是他這麼在意那款飲料的部分原因。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"What do you think of the purple drink in the machine by the gym?\" Coco asked the first student.",
      "zh": "Coco 問第一個學生：「你覺得體育館那台機器裡的紫色飲料怎麼樣？」"
    },
    {
      "en": "The student made a face before answering. \"Too sweet,\" he said. \"Way too sweet.\"",
      "zh": "那個學生回答前先做了個表情：「太甜了，」他說：「甜到不行。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "The second student agreed completely. The third student had never even noticed it existed.",
      "zh": "第二個學生完全同意，第三個學生根本沒注意過它的存在。"
    },
    {
      "en": "By the fifth answer, Bernice was laughing. \"It's not a mystery,\" she said. \"It's just a drink nobody else likes.\"",
      "zh": "問到第五個答案時，Bernice 已經笑了出來：「這根本不是謎團，」她說：「只是一款沒有其他人喜歡的飲料。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Coco laughed too, but she still wrote one more question in her notebook: if the answer was this simple, why did it feel like such a good case?",
      "zh": "Coco 也笑了，但她還是在筆記本上多寫了一個問題：如果答案這麼簡單，為什麼感覺起來卻像是一個這麼好的案子？"
    },
    {
      "en": "They found the student who wrote the note, a quiet boy from another class named Wei.",
      "zh": "他們找到寫紙條的那個學生，另一班一個安靜的男生，名叫 Wei。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"So... nobody else likes it,\" Coco told him gently. \"That's really the whole answer.\"",
      "zh": "Coco 溫和地告訴他：「所以⋯⋯沒有其他人喜歡它，這就是全部的答案了。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Wei didn't look upset at all. He looked calm instead.",
      "zh": "Wei 一點也不覺得難過，反而看起來很平靜。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"I thought maybe the machine was going to stop selling it,\" he said. \"I check almost every day, just in case.\"",
      "zh": "他說：「我以為機器可能會停賣這款飲料，我幾乎每天都會去看一下，以防萬一。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Why would it stop selling it if it never runs out?\" Bernice asked.",
      "zh": "Bernice 問：「如果它永遠不會賣完，為什麼會停賣？」"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"I don't know,\" Wei admitted. \"I guess I just worry about things staying the same.\"",
      "zh": "Wei 承認：「我不知道，我猜我只是會擔心事情能不能一直維持一樣。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "For a moment, nobody said anything.",
      "zh": "有那麼一刻，誰都沒有開口。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Well,\" Coco said finally, \"as long as other people keep disliking it, your drink is safe forever.\"",
      "zh": "Coco 最後說：「這樣的話，只要其他人繼續不喜歡它，你的飲料就永遠安全了。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Wei actually laughed, which surprised all three of them.",
      "zh": "Wei 真的笑了出來，這讓他們三個人都很意外。"
    },
    {
      "en": "On their next episode, Coco and Bernice told this story differently from the first two.",
      "zh": "在下一集裡，Coco 和 Bernice 講這個故事的方式跟前兩次不一樣。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"Not every mystery has a hidden hero,\" Coco said into the microphone. \"Sometimes the answer is just: not many people share your taste, and that's fine.\"",
      "zh": "Coco 對著麥克風說：「不是每個謎團背後都有一個隱藏的英雄，有時候答案只是:沒有多少人跟你口味一樣,而這樣也沒關係。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Bernice added her own line. \"Also, we drank four cans of it during this investigation. It really is too sweet.\"",
      "zh": "Bernice 補了一句:「而且,我們在查這個案子的時候喝了四罐,真的太甜了。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "The class laughed harder at that episode than at any before it.",
      "zh": "全班聽這一集笑得比之前任何一集都大聲。"
    },
    {
      "en": "After class, Mr. Pan told them something they hadn't expected. \"Three cases,\" he said. \"And three different kinds of true.\"",
      "zh": "下課後,潘老師說了一句他們沒想到的話:「三個案子,」他說:「三種不同的真相。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Coco wrote his words in her notebook without fully understanding them yet.",
      "zh": "Coco 把他的話寫進筆記本裡,雖然還沒完全弄懂那句話的意思。"
    },
    {
      "en": "That evening, the Friday Box held a single new note, shorter than any before it.",
      "zh": "那天傍晚,星期五箱子裡有一張新紙條,比之前任何一張都短。"
    },
    {
      "en": "It said only: \"Ask about the fourth floor stairs. Nobody uses them. Nobody says why.\"",
      "zh": "上面只寫著:「去查查四樓的樓梯,沒有人會用它,也沒有人說為什麼。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "Wei's older sister was a doctor, and she always told him breakfast was the most important meal.",
      "zh": "Wei 的姊姊是醫生，她總是告訴他早餐是一天中最重要的一餐。"
    },
    {
      "en": "\"I'm not lazy,\" Wei said, laughing. \"I just really love that drink.\"",
      "zh": "Wei 笑著說：「我不是懶惰，我只是真的很愛那款飲料。」"
    },
    {
      "en": "The school nurse joked that Wei's real illness was simply loving one drink a little too much.",
      "zh": "校護開玩笑說，Wei 真正的毛病只是太愛一款飲料而已。"
    }
  ],
